00:36:06.690 --> 00:36:08.320
is you called it out, right?

00:36:08.320 --> 00:36:09.370
Which was kind of what
we were talking about.

00:36:09.370 --> 00:36:12.010
So there's kind of a vote for
the column of just call it out.

00:36:12.010 --> 00:36:13.860
Be brave and call it out.

00:36:13.860 --> 00:36:17.860
Secondly, I have had that
conversation two-fold.

00:36:17.860 --> 00:36:20.840
One was about the F-word.

00:36:20.840 --> 00:36:23.420
So when I took over
a team, I came in,

00:36:23.420 --> 00:36:26.140
and actually the CEO departed.

00:36:26.140 --> 00:36:27.140
He was the founding CEO.

00:36:27.140 --> 00:36:28.290
It was really rough.

00:36:28.290 --> 00:36:30.899
And I came in, and I
found that there was

00:36:30.899 --> 00:36:32.190
a lot of really rough language.

00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:34.530
And I just said, hey,
guys, just so you know,

00:36:34.530 --> 00:36:38.560
when you speak to me using that
word, the effectiveness of what

00:36:38.560 --> 00:36:40.840
you're trying to
communicate to me drops.

00:36:40.840 --> 00:36:44.770
So either you're OK with that
or just take it in consideration

00:36:44.770 --> 00:36:48.120
if you want me to act the way--
if you want to influence me,

00:36:48.120 --> 00:36:49.510
don't use that word.

00:36:49.510 --> 00:36:51.260
Second one was the word "hero."

00:36:51.260 --> 00:36:53.380
We had a hero culture.

00:36:53.380 --> 00:36:54.780
And here's what I think.

00:36:54.780 --> 00:36:56.610
When you have a hero
culture or a rock star

00:36:56.610 --> 00:36:58.850
or whatever, I don't
think it's bad to say

00:36:58.850 --> 00:37:02.610
to someone in my team,
oh, you're a rock star.

00:37:02.610 --> 00:37:04.470
Your contribution was great.

00:37:04.470 --> 00:37:06.980
But when you're talking
about the whole culture,

00:37:06.980 --> 00:37:10.220
a hero culture is the opposite
of a teamwork culture.

00:37:10.220 --> 00:37:11.910
And what I had to
get people to realize

00:37:11.910 --> 00:37:14.840
is you guys are
promoting that someone

00:37:14.840 --> 00:37:16.530
has to come in
and save our bacon

00:37:16.530 --> 00:37:18.400
through their
individual efforts.

00:37:18.400 --> 00:37:21.570
And what that's depriving
us of is a strong team,

00:37:21.570 --> 00:37:24.652
because a strong team
never gets to that point.

00:37:24.652 --> 00:37:26.110
So we've got to
figure out whenever

00:37:26.110 --> 00:37:28.054
we see this hero behavior
having to come in,

00:37:28.054 --> 00:37:29.220
we've got to figure out why.

00:37:29.220 --> 00:37:31.660
That's a signal that
something's not working.

00:37:31.660 --> 00:37:33.770
So it's not exactly the
dictionary conversation

00:37:33.770 --> 00:37:34.920
I think that you had.

00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:36.860
But I love that
you called it out.

00:37:36.860 --> 00:37:39.300
Call it for what it is and
talk about effectiveness.

00:37:39.300 --> 00:37:41.910
Is it making as effective as
a team to keep going like this

00:37:41.910 --> 00:37:42.496
or not?

00:37:42.496 --> 00:37:44.370
And everybody's team's
going to be different.

00:37:44.370 --> 00:37:49.179
What your teams
tolerate-- so some teams

00:37:49.179 --> 00:37:50.220
might say, you know what?

00:37:50.220 --> 00:37:53.429
I'm a ninja, or I'm
the princess of data.

00:37:53.429 --> 00:37:54.970
That's awesome if
that works for them

00:37:54.970 --> 00:37:56.219
and that's effective for them.

00:37:56.219 --> 00:37:58.550
But another team might have
those exact same constructs

00:37:58.550 --> 00:38:00.080
and go, wait a minute.

00:38:00.080 --> 00:38:01.370
That's not effective for us.

00:38:01.370 --> 00:38:04.216
We do not want to be called data
princesses or whatever it is.

00:38:04.216 --> 00:38:06.340
But somebody else might
say, yes, that's what I am,

00:38:06.340 --> 00:38:07.450
and I rock it.

00:38:07.450 --> 00:38:09.270
So it's all local.

00:38:09.270 --> 00:38:10.947
Don't be afraid to call it out.

00:38:10.947 --> 00:38:13.280
And I think that's the whole
message is have the courage

00:38:13.280 --> 00:38:16.570
to call it out.

